Alongside my studies, I’ve gained hands-on experience through my role as a student worker in an animal research lab at LSU, as well as through various volunteer positions and jobs. I also serve on the executive board of the Student National Association for Black Veterinarians (SNAVB), where I help advocate for diversity in the field. Beyond my love for animals, I’m deeply committed to inspiring young women of color to pursue careers in STEM, demonstrating that they can thrive in spaces where they are often underrepresented.

I am a member of the club lacrosse team, and a freshman chair for the Foundation for International Medical Relief of Children club (FIMRC). Outside of the classroom I love to spend time with my friends exploring Pittsburgh, watch sports, and be outside.

name: Jenna
bio: My name is Jenna Long and I am currently an incoming third year at UC Davis. I am originally from a beach city in the Los Angeles area so, going to the beach with friends/living near the ocean has always been a big part of my identity. Music has also always been a very important part of my life and I can play both the piano and guitar. Going into my third year, I am hoping to conquer my stage fright and join a student band or even find other friends I can casually play with and listen to music with! This past summer in 2024, I studied abroad in Barcelona, where I was able to practice my Spanish, meet people from all over the world, and experience a big city with so much life and so rich in culture. Moving to UC Davis was definitely a big transition but one I didn't anticipate on loving so much. I quickly fell in love with the small town vibes despite growing up in a big city my whole life. I feel like UC Davis and living in a small town has really allowed me to meet so many people ranging from different interests to all different backgrounds and yet, become such a close, tight community that can come together and appreciate the unique charm of small town Davis.

name: Charlie Berry

I am currently looking into pursing law school after my undergrad at UMD!

However, I discovered a deep passion for weightlifting. Currently, I’m a junior at NYU Stern, majoring in Finance with a co-concentration in Entrepreneurship. My experiences at NYU have been incredible, and I feel truly blessed to attend my dream school.

I was a part of the STEP program my incoming freshman year of college which helped me gain a lot of helpful information about Davis. I like to spend most of my time talking about my campus to friends and family members when going back home to visit. I have helped a few of my friends who are planning on attending UC Davis with any questions they have regarding the campus. Even though I wasn't fully involved in my first year of college, I was able to explore my campus and learn about the numerous resources we have to offer.

At my previous high school, I participated in speech and art competitions, led a theater society as President, hosted events, and managed a team of students. I also actively participated in community service events, demonstrating leadership, creativity, and a commitment to making a positive impact. At UMKC, I will be pursuing my bachelor's degree in Mathematics and Statistics and look forward to participating in fun and engaging societies, as well as becoming a peer tutor.

name: Shreyas
bio: Hi, My name is Shreyas. I am currently a senior studying physics and statistics at the University of Illinois. I am interested in pursuing a career in Computational sciences, specifically using computational methods to solve engineering or scientific problems. I am involved on campus working two jobs one in admissions and one in research. My hobbies include vegetarian cooking and working out.

name: Kristina Barron
bio: Hello, my name is Kristina Barron, and I love to tell you a bit about my self. I am an upcoming Freshman at Texas State University in San Marcos, TX. my major is B.F.A in theatre with a performance and production concentration. I love acting,music,fashion.

name: Priscilla Ye
bio: Hi, my name is Priscilla Ye from Laurel, Maryland, and I'm a current sophomore at Cornell. I am currently pursuing a major in chemical engineering and a possible minor in applied mathematics. I look forward to helping you get to know everything there is to know about Cornell!

name: Demian Ramesar
bio: Currently study Biology at Montclair State University, looking to help incoming freshmen learn about the University and what it has to offer. I am very detail oriented and very knowledgeable about the University.

name: Hannah Bauer
bio: Hi! My name is Hannah Bauer and I am a rising JR at UCF working on the campus ambassador team at the main campus and the Rosen  College of hospitality management. Studying entertainment management as a major with a theatre minor, I have a passion for hospitality and working alongside guests. I am super energetic and bubbly. In the past few years as being a tour guide already, I can admit I absolutely love it and would love to continue my passion while still at the university !

name: Daniel Novick
bio: Hi, my name is Daniel, and I am a Junior at Lehigh! I am majoring in Computer Science and Business with a minor in Data Science. I am also involved with the Office of First Year Experience and greek life. I love showing prospective students around the Lehigh campus!

name: Vivian Beck
bio: I am a Sophomore at UW Madison and I love to tell people about it! I am also on the club swim team, in a service fraternity, and in various other clubs. I enjoy a school-fun balance and this school is definitely the place for that!

name: Pranavi Sakhamuri
bio: I am a passionate and experienced college student with a strong background in leadership and communication. As a student leader, I’ve guided peers and new students, helping them navigate campus life and academics. My roles at a museum’s front desk and as a hospital volunteer have further sharpened my interpersonal skills. I’m knowledgeable about my campus and eager to share my insights with prospective students. Reliable, enthusiastic, and committed, I’m excited about the opportunity to positively impact others’ college decisions as a Campus Tour Guide with TouredIt.

name: Harlem Taylor
bio: Howdy! My name is Harlem Taylor and I am a sophomore and Danforth Scholar at WashU. After a long time spent figuring out my academic interests, I'm currently studying economics, statistics, and marketing. Outside of class, I work a few on-campus jobs that allow me to understand the institution and its student body more holistically. In my free time I'm often at a WashU hosted event or spending time with my friends.

name: Cassidy Cashion
bio: I am a senior in the Boston College Carroll School of Management co-concentrating in Finance and Accounting for Finance and Consulting with a minor in Philosophy. The past semester I studied abroad in Parma, Italy! I am involved in the Student Admission Program and Women in Business clubs on campus. In my free time, I enjoy going to the gym and into Boston with friends!

name: Trent Bunker
bio: I’m a senior at Tufts studying Political Science and History. After graduation, I’ll be attending Harvard Law School following a stint on Capitol Hill. I’m involved in political advocacy on campus, as well as a member of the club lacrosse and rugby teams. In my free time, I like to weightlift, read political philosophy and theology, and watch college football.

name: Dylan Senescall
bio: Hello! My name is Dylan and I am a student at Georgetown University, studying psychology on the pre-med track. I hold research assistant positions for a project on social determinants of health and child wellbeing funded by the Health Resources and Services Administration, and for Georgetown's Lab on Social and Affective Neuroscience. I also work at the campus gym and am involved with a few academic and social clubs on campus. Over the summers at home in Seattle, I have gotten a certification as a nursing assistant and plan on applying to work in a hospital. In my free time, I enjoy running and other exercise, reading, and trying the different restaurants, cafes and bakeries in Georgetown/D.C!

name: Isabella Ilvento
bio: I am a sophomore at the University of Delaware. My major is one of the top programs in the country and it is limited to only 30 kids per grade.  My major is so unique and offers so many great opportunities. I have my real estate license, and have been very involved in that. I am in greek life annd actively participate in our events. I am fun and outgoing and love my school! I am positive and kind and would love to show someone my school!

name: Rylee Garrett
bio: I am a student at Montclair university perusing a degree in journalism with a focus on creative writing! I have plenty of experience in the communications field on and off camera. And I have been told that I am a very organized and positive person.

name: Brooke Skarda
bio: Originally from Minnetonka, Minnesota. I'm entering my sophomore year at TCU and am pursuing a finance degree, but also involved in Greek life in a variety of different extracurricular activities.

name: James Park
bio: Hello! I am a senior at Emory University and I come from Saipan, a small island in the Pacific. I am working towards a BS in Quantitative Sciences: Informatics and a Minor in Spanish. My academic interests are computer science and data science. During my free time, I enjoy playing instruments, playing games, and trying out different food places in Atlanta!

name: Bella MacWilliams
bio: Hello! My name is Bella, and I’m a Junior at MSU! I know my way around campus very well, and I love meeting new people, especially when I get to help them out! Montclair has a beautiful campus, and I'd be happy to show it off to anyone interested!

name: Adriana Pinedo-Colon
school: Rutgers, The State University of New Jersey
bio: My name is Adriana and I am a person of diverse interests. I am passionate not only about nutrition, but about cooking, playing guitar, traveling, reading about various topics, and learning languages. I have been able to explore my interests partly thanks to enrichment opportunities provided by my university, and my cultural background (Puerto Rican and Mexican). I am hardworking, responsible, outspoken, and love asking/answering questions. I excel at writing, and I greatly enjoy teaching others about topics that I am knowledgeable about.

name: Harry Davidson

I love traveling, hiking, and trying new foods, and my academic interests include economics, psychology, business, and government. Outside of the classroom, I spend my free time hanging out with friends, playing sports, and rooting for the DC sports teams.

name: Jacklyn Helbourg
bio: I am an upcoming freshman at URI and look forward to getting involved on campus. I enjoy working with others and meeting new people. I am always up for a challenge and will face them head on. While I am someone who tends to stick to a small group of friends but I am always ready and willing to make friends with others.

name: Brandon Wang
bio: Hi, my name is Brandon, and I'm a sophomore at USC. It was my dream school and I'm extremely passionate about it. I'm well versed in the student life here, having joined a fraternity and attended many athletic events. I know the campus very well and would love to show people around.

name: Blake Bilik
school: Rutgers, The State University of New Jersey
bio: I am a freshman at the School of Arts and Sciences at Rutgers NB. I worked at the YMCA for two years. I am undecided but will probably study psychology and a major or minor.

name: Vivian Grange
bio: Hello! My name is Vivian and I am a Freshman at NAU. I love college and all the people and experiences you can meet. I am hardworking, organized, and kind. I also have worked in customer service for two years so it would be in my comfort zone.

name: Xiaoyuan Wang

I also have experiences in tutoring k-12 students with mandarin, english and various mathematic courses, as well as customer service skills accumulated through working at Chipotle and dining halls.

name: Anton Cook

I would love to give tours to students through this program and allow them that opportunity.

name: Kasey E Smith

I've worked in a restaurant as a hostess for the past year and a half, which has taught me many important skills including punctuality,  team-work, and most importantly, social skills.

name: Cece Chao
bio: Hi! My name is Cece and I'm a senior at UC Santa Barbara. I'm majoring in history and have been working on an independent thesis project. I really love this school and I hope that I can convince you to come here to study!

name: Grace Sams

name: Ariana Dickey

name: Reef Mordente

I have been dancing competitively since I was 7 years old and I am now a second year on the UM Sunsations Dance Team. We attend every home football and basketball game, along with travel, volunteer opportunities, competition, and other school performances. Being an athlete, an active member of Alpha Delta Pi sorority, and business student, I have extremely good time management and organization skills.

name: Natalie Wu
bio: Hi, my name is Natalie and I am a sophomore at UC Davis hoping to double-major in Psychology and Sociology (originally enrolled as an East Asian Studies major, but in the process of switching). I am very interested in humanitarian work and hopefully studying abroad. One of the main reasons why I chose Davis was because I love the calm, low-key campus!

name: Caitlyn O’Boyle

name: Hannah Caldwell

name: Yuhuan Dan

In my free time, I enjoy spending time with friends, exploring new interests, and going into Boston.

bio: I am current third year at USC studying International Relations on the Pre-Law Track. On the weekends I love to cafe hop or go to our football games!

I also enjoy playing tennis, baking, and spending time with friends and family. I'm incredibly eager to share my love of Tufts with others!

name: Old Account
bio: Bio

My plan for after college is to become a child and family therapist.

name: Alaina Snow

I absolutely love UW’s campus and have given many of my own tours to potential students. I’m a huge Badger basketball fan and have gone to every home football game since freshman year.

bio: Hi, my name is Ki'Shon Davis and I am an incoming freshman for UNLV. I have a great amount of experience with customer service and positive attitude as well as communication skills. I'm athletic, academic, and very social.

name: Bryan Cisneros
bio: I am 23 years old. I've been at CSULA for 6 years so I know the campus pretty well.

name: Charliene Lien

name: Kelcey Dion

I spend a lot of my free time as a member of the Women's Lacrosse team here at Middlebury.  I also love to hike, ski, & enjoy the beautiful outdoors of Vermont! Last year I had the incredible opportunity to study abroad in a fully immersive program in Madrid, Spain.  Feel free to ask me all things about athletics, study abroad, or the best places to eat in town!  I can't wait to tour you around Middlebury!!

name: Mathilde Hebras
bio: Hi! I'm Mathilde, I am a French-American student at UCLA. I study International Development Studies and am pursuing a Professional Writing Minor. I'm interested in foreign service and potentially going to law school for international law.

name: Kiran Lutchman
bio: My name is Kiran Lutchman and I am a Nutrition and Food Science Major at LSU. I chose to come to Baton Rouge for university because the programs in my field and the rich culture. I am looking to further my education at LSU since my undergraduate time is coming to an end. My hobbies include working out, community service, and cutting hair.

name: Christian Lebron
bio: I am a sophomore at Connecticut College studying Audio Engineering and Economics. I have a well rounded experience of my school through these drastically different passions of mine and with that well rounded experience I believe I can showcase my schools pros and cons extremely well.

name: Isaac
bio: Howdy my name is Isaac and I'm currently a freshman at Appalachian state. Before coming here I worked construction in both my civilian life and military. I hope to get my degree in history so that one day I can teach at a university.

name: Audrey Garfinkel
bio: Hi, my name is Audrey Garfinkel. I am a Junior dance and education double major at the University of Massachusetts Amherst, and I am also a member of the Commonwealth Honors College. Aside from dancing and working with kids, I love learning Spanish and hope to travel to Madrid someday. My favorite thing about college is being able to do so many different things, like going surfing or learning to belly dance!

name: Jordan Garrison

In my free time, I enjoy hanging out with my cat and doing as many cool things as I can. I love gaining new experiences and helping others gain them as well. I would be ecstatic to help you find your place here at KSU! May you learn to love it as much as we all do!

name: Samantha Alter
bio: Hi! My name is Samantha Alter and I am a sophomore studying at the University of Rhode Island. I am majoring in communicative disorders (speech-language pathology) am minoring in special populations. On campus I am an RAM (resident academic mentor) for health sciences LLC. My job is an lived in position where I am available for students questions about academics. I am also there to make sure that my first-year students are comfortable in their new setting. I create fun programs such as DIY scrub night, spooktacular Halloween party, academic advising and more! Besides being an RAM, I'm involved in intramurals, SOLC, URISSHLA, in the process of becoming a Delta Epsilon Mu member, Hillel, adventure club, puppy raisers and more! Also, I like to hang out with friends, explore Rhode Island, and go to URI events (such as ice-skating at the Boss Arena). Please feel free to contact me using the information below if you have any questions!

name: sarah kenvin
bio: Hi! My name is Sarah Kenvin and I am a sophomore at Wake Forest University. I have recently been accepted as a tour guide, and am excited as I have begun my training. Would love to be able to show off my beautiful campus to as many people as possible!

name: Emma Wilkie
bio: I am a senior at William & Mary. Aside from extracurriculars I am involved in a psychology lab and am completing an honors thesis in linguistics. I also enjoy writing and taking walks around campus.
secondary_major: Linguistics and Comparative Language and Literature

name: Alison Garcia
bio: I'm an 18 year old studying business administration at Cal Baptist. Im originally from New York. Ive been working since I was 14 years old, I have customer service experience. Ive also had internships and been involved in many clubs.

name: Fareen Dhuka
bio: Alongside advocacy of accessible healthcare and voicing minority experiences, something I value most in life is forming genuine relationships with others. I'm currently applying to medical schools and love to intertwine my passion for medicine and digital media as an intern with the Lindau Lab. My dream retirement hustle is wedding planning, so I can continue creating wax seal calligraphy invitations photographing engagements for my photography company! I also participate in research, dance, pediatric volunteering, campus publications, and weightlifting in my free time. I'm very excited to give tours of my school's campus and recommend some great Chicago food spots!

name: Maddie Vercher
bio: Hello! My name is Maddie, and I am a sophomore at Cornell from Tampa, Florida. I’m majoring in Mechanical Engineering with a minor in Business. I’m excited to show you the wonderful Cornell campus and all of its incredible programs and colleges or chat on the phone and give you all the information you're looking for :)

name: Katie Schrader
bio: I am currently a third-year student at Northeastern University with an interest in international law, legislative drafting, diplomacy, and public policy, specifically in the United Nations. Through coursework at Northeastern University as well as at John Cabot University in Rome, Italy, I have developed a deep understanding and interest in intercultural communication and negotiations. I have also gained knowledge on topics such as Public-Private Partnerships, Climate Change Policy, and Public Procurement through my internship at the International Law Institute. I am studying to become an international lawyer or diplomat and have experience in environmental research, research writing, and data management along with leadership and organizational skills developed through years of project development and volunteering.

name: Yaduveer Singh
bio:
I’m a junior at Emory University’s Goizueta Business School, majoring in business administration with a focus on finance and consulting and minoring in quantitative sciences. I’m active in the Indian Cultural Association (ICA), helping plan Emory’s largest off-campus event, Diwali Night. As the past president of the Oxford Investment Management Group (OIMG), I expanded the club to include students within and outside the business school, broadening access to investment experience.

Outside of school, I’ve been a GMIT analyst at Nomura, where I enhanced the speed of mortgage-backed securities analysis, and an SBA intern at Magyar Bank, streamlining loan processes for small businesses in New Jersey. For fun, I enjoy playing tennis, going to the gym, cooking, and traveling.

name: Alex McCauley
bio: I am a Junior at Muhlenberg majoring in Economics and minoring in Statistics. I am co-captain of the Men's golf team and am also a successful photographer who is currently working on a book. I was an orientation leader this year so I am an experienced tour guide.

bio: dsfd
